  {
    "id": "kp-Y10.6-01",
    "section": "Y10.6",
    "order": 1,
    "title": "Sine and Cosine Rules",
    "title_zh": "正弦与余弦定理",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "For non-right-angled triangles with sides $a, b, c$ opposite angles $A, B, C$:\n\n**The Sine Rule** is $\\frac{a}{\\sin A} = \\frac{b}{\\sin B} = \\frac{c}{\\sin C}$. Use this when you know an opposite side-angle pair.\n\n**The Cosine Rule** is $a^2 = b^2 + c^2 - 2bc \\cos A$. Use this when you have SAS (two sides and the included angle) to find the third side, or SSS (three sides) to find an angle.\n\n**Area of a triangle** can be calculated using $\\text{Area} = \\frac{1}{2}ab \\sin C$.",
      "zh": "对于边长为 $a, b, c$ 且对应角为 $A, B, C$ 的非直角三角形：\n\n**正弦定理**为 $\\frac{a}{\\sin A} = \\frac{b}{\\sin B} = \\frac{c}{\\sin C}$。当你已知一组对应的边角对时使用此定理。\n\n**余弦定理**为 $a^2 = b^2 + c^2 - 2bc \\cos A$。当你已知 SAS（两边及其夹角）求第三边，或已知 SSS（三边）求角时使用此定理。\n\n**三角形面积**可以使用公式 $\\text{面积} = \\frac{1}{2}ab \\sin C$ 计算。"
    },
    "examPatterns": [
      {
        "id": "ep-trig-rules",
        "label": "Solve non-right-angled triangles",
        "label_zh": "解非直角三角形",
        "description": "Calculate missing lengths and angles using Sine or Cosine rules.",
        "description_zh": "使用正弦或余弦定理计算缺失的边长和角度。"
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "patternId": "ep-trig-rules",
        "question": "In triangle $ABC$, $AB = 7$ cm, $BC = 10$ cm, and angle $ABC = 60^\\circ$. Find the length of $AC$.",
        "question_zh": "在三角形 $ABC$ 中，$AB = 7$ cm，$BC = 10$ cm，且角 $ABC = 60^\\circ$。求 $AC$ 的长度。",
        "solution": "**Step 1:** We have two sides and the included angle (SAS), so use the Cosine Rule.\n$AC^2 = 7^2 + 10^2 - 2(7)(10) \\cos 60^\\circ$\n\n**Step 2:** Calculate values:\n$AC^2 = 49 + 100 - 140(0.5)$\n$AC^2 = 149 - 70 = 79$\n\n**Step 3:** Take the square root:\n$AC = \\sqrt{79} \\approx 8.89$ cm.\n\n**Answer:** $8.89$ cm",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：** 我们已知两边及其夹角 (SAS)，因此使用余弦定理。\n$AC^2 = 7^2 + 10^2 - 2(7)(10) \\cos 60^\\circ$。\n\n**步骤2：** 计算数值：\n$AC^2 = 49 + 100 - 140(0.5)$\n$AC^2 = 149 - 70 = 79$。\n\n**步骤3：** 开平方：\n$AC = \\sqrt{79} \\approx 8.89$ cm。\n\n**答案：** $8.89$ cm",
        "source": "Year 10 Assessment"
      },
      {
        "patternId": "ep-trig-rules",
        "question": "In triangle $PQR$, angle $P = 40^\\circ$, angle $Q = 80^\\circ$, and $QR = 5$ cm. Find the length of $PR$.",
        "question_zh": "在三角形 $PQR$ 中，角 $P = 40^\\circ$，角 $Q = 80^\\circ$，且 $QR = 5$ cm。求 $PR$ 的长度。",
        "solution": "**Step 1:** Use the Sine Rule. Side $QR$ is opposite angle $P$, and side $PR$ is opposite angle $Q$.\n$\\frac{PR}{\\sin 80^\\circ} = \\frac{5}{\\sin 40^\\circ}$\n\n**Step 2:** Rearrange to find $PR$:\n$PR = \\frac{5 \\sin 80^\\circ}{\\sin 40^\\circ}$\n\n**Step 3:** Calculate:\n$PR \\approx \\frac{5 \\times 0.9848}{0.6428} \\approx 7.66$ cm.\n\n**Answer:** $7.66$ cm",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：** 使用正弦定理。边 $QR$ 对应角 $P$，边 $PR$ 对应角 $Q$。\n$\\frac{PR}{\\sin 80^\\circ} = \\frac{5}{\\sin 40^\\circ}$。\n\n**步骤2：** 整理求 $PR$：\n$PR = \\frac{5 \\sin 80^\\circ}{\\sin 40^\\circ}$。\n\n**步骤3：** 计算：\n$PR \\approx \\frac{5 \\times 0.9848}{0.6428} \\approx 7.66$ cm。\n\n**答案：** $7.66$ cm",
        "source": "Adapted from Y10 curriculum"
      }
    ],
    "testYourself": [
      {
        "q": "Which rule is best for finding an angle if you know all three sides of a triangle?",
        "q_zh": "如果已知三角形的三条边，哪种定理最适合求角？",
        "o": [
